1
00:00:14,667 --> 00:00:18,433
We're ready for tonight,
even if it gets dark here.

2
00:00:18,567 --> 00:00:20,667
I wish you were here, baby.

3
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,933
This place is so peaceful.

4
00:00:23,067 --> 00:00:25,933
I will be happy and content
on this island

5
00:00:26,067 --> 00:00:27,633
as long as you're with me.

6
00:00:27,767 --> 00:00:29,433
You're all I need,
my dear child.

7
00:00:29,567 --> 00:00:31,367
Where else can she go?

8
00:00:31,500 --> 00:00:33,200
We are her only family.

9
00:00:33,333 --> 00:00:35,600
She's been like this
since she was young.

10
00:00:35,767 --> 00:00:40,400
She goes away whenever
she feels sad or has a problem.

11
00:00:40,533 --> 00:00:41,900
But she comes back, Amanda.

12
00:00:42,033 --> 00:00:43,400
I promise.

13
00:00:43,533 --> 00:00:45,333
My goodness, Eden.

14
00:00:45,467 --> 00:00:48,933
You came here to find peace.

15
00:00:49,067 --> 00:00:51,833
Not to find someone
who isn't here.

16
00:00:55,733 --> 00:00:56,467
Why are you here?

17
00:00:56,600 --> 00:00:57,900
How did you know I'm here?

18
00:00:58,033 --> 00:01:00,500
Even Raichu has no
idea where I am.

19
00:01:00,633 --> 00:01:01,733
Because I love you.

20
00:01:01,867 --> 00:01:03,433
I listened to what you said.

21
00:01:03,567 --> 00:01:05,933
And I realized that this is
where you going to go

22
00:01:06,067 --> 00:01:07,367
to get some peace.

23
00:01:07,533 --> 00:01:09,600
Yen, let's just use
this time to talk.

24
00:01:09,733 --> 00:01:13,033
I have a lot to tell you
about the video you saw.

25
00:01:13,167 --> 00:01:14,200
I'll be right here.

26
00:01:14,333 --> 00:01:15,567
I'm staying here
until you talk to me.

27
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:16,867
I'm not going anywhere.

28
00:01:17,000 --> 00:01:20,133
He would answer because he
knows I'm worried about him.

29
00:01:20,267 --> 00:01:21,933
His phone must have died.

30
00:01:22,067 --> 00:01:23,300
Or something like that.

31
00:01:23,433 --> 00:01:26,300
If something bad happens to my
son while looking for Eden,

32
00:01:26,433 --> 00:01:27,600
I swear!

33
00:01:27,733 --> 00:01:31,500
How she wishes that she'd
moved back with her mother!

34
00:01:31,633 --> 00:01:33,700
Are you going to
let me in now?

35
00:01:33,833 --> 00:01:35,333
Are you waiting
for an invitation?

36
00:01:35,467 --> 00:01:38,367
I'm soaking wet. Your tent might
get wet if I come inside.

37
00:01:38,500 --> 00:01:39,600
Just get inside.

38
00:01:39,733 --> 00:01:44,133
This is the place where
Rina and Zandro tortured me.

39
00:01:44,300 --> 00:01:45,533
Just stay here.

40
00:01:45,667 --> 00:01:48,467
Don't come inside if you
can't handle it yet.

41
00:01:48,600 --> 00:01:52,900
We can't waste everything that
we've been through together.

42
00:01:53,033 --> 00:01:55,533
I can't forget everything
that you said, Red.

43
00:01:55,667 --> 00:01:57,333
Sab edited the video.

44
00:01:57,467 --> 00:01:58,500
This is what
really happened.

45
00:01:58,633 --> 00:01:59,733
You have to see
the whole video.

46
00:01:59,867 --> 00:02:02,433
Come on!

47
00:02:02,567 --> 00:02:04,867
I won't have to
change diapers.

48
00:02:05,000 --> 00:02:06,900
No baby bottles to make.

49
00:02:08,567 --> 00:02:10,567
Because my baby's gone.

50
00:02:10,700 --> 00:02:13,467
I thought we could
overcome everything

51
00:02:13,600 --> 00:02:15,400
as long as we were together.

52
00:02:15,567 --> 00:02:20,633
Because we promised each
other that we'd stay together.

53
00:02:20,767 --> 00:02:23,033
That we'd be together.

54
00:02:23,167 --> 00:02:24,100
Red!

55
00:02:24,233 --> 00:02:25,767
I'm sorry!

56
00:02:25,900 --> 00:02:27,333
I'm sorry.

57
00:02:29,267 --> 00:02:30,267
Tell me the truth!

58
00:02:31,200 --> 00:02:32,400
- Who told you to do this?
- It's Elmer!

59
00:02:32,533 --> 00:02:34,100
We have to help him.

60
00:02:35,367 --> 00:02:36,567
Let's go.

61
00:02:39,233 --> 00:02:40,267
I'm sorry.

62
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:42,733
I thought it was real
because it was a video.

63
00:02:42,867 --> 00:02:43,933
Sabina showed me that.

64
00:02:44,067 --> 00:02:45,067
I'm sorry.

65
00:02:46,133 --> 00:02:47,700
- Sabina is evil.
- It's okay.

66
00:02:47,867 --> 00:02:48,467
I'm sorry.

67
00:02:48,600 --> 00:02:51,400
Yen, it's okay.
It's okay.

68
00:02:51,533 --> 00:02:52,300
It's not your fault.

69
00:02:52,433 --> 00:02:53,933
And I don't blame you.

70
00:02:55,933 --> 00:02:57,767
What's important is you already
know the truth.

71
00:02:59,200 --> 00:03:01,133
That I can never hurt you.

72
00:03:03,333 --> 00:03:05,733
Yen, I love you so much.

73
00:03:07,633 --> 00:03:10,067
And I love our
child so much.

74
00:03:10,933 --> 00:03:13,100
I was in so much pain
when we lost her.

75
00:03:15,367 --> 00:03:20,033
But I tried to be tough for you.

76
00:03:21,700 --> 00:03:24,633
Because I know you have no one
else to rely on but me.

77
00:03:26,800 --> 00:03:28,200
I'm sorry, Red.

78
00:03:28,333 --> 00:03:29,100
It's okay.

79
00:03:30,133 --> 00:03:32,100
I love you so much.

80
00:03:32,967 --> 00:03:39,533
I'm sorry for punishing you
for something you didn't do.

81
00:03:39,667 --> 00:03:41,733
I won't do it again, okay?

82
00:03:41,867 --> 00:03:43,300
I'm sorry.

83
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:46,500
It's okay.

84
00:04:16,833 --> 00:04:18,000
What?

85
00:04:18,133 --> 00:04:19,500
What do you mean you
don't know anything?

86
00:04:20,533 --> 00:04:22,100
Tell me the truth.

87
00:04:22,233 --> 00:04:24,233
I don't know anything!

88
00:04:24,367 --> 00:04:25,867
Let me go!
I don't know anything!

89
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:27,900
Zandro told me that
you're a coward!

90
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:29,667
You didn't do this alone.

91
00:04:29,800 --> 00:04:31,867
Who made you do this?

92
00:04:43,233 --> 00:04:44,033
No one!

93
00:04:44,167 --> 00:04:45,133
Tell me the truth!

94
00:04:45,267 --> 00:04:46,333
No! I don't know anything!
Don't do this!

95
00:04:46,467 --> 00:04:47,667
I'll make a countdown.

96
00:04:47,800 --> 00:04:48,867
Please, no!

97
00:04:49,000 --> 00:04:49,800
One!
Have mercy on me!

98
00:04:50,733 --> 00:04:51,967
- Answer her!
- Please, no!

99
00:04:52,100 --> 00:04:53,967
I don't know anything!

100
00:04:54,100 --> 00:04:54,900
Two!
Tell her!

101
00:04:55,900 --> 00:04:57,167
I don't know anything!

102
00:04:59,900 --> 00:05:00,433
Hey!

103
00:05:02,000 --> 00:05:02,733
Stop that!

104
00:05:03,700 --> 00:05:04,833
Put your gun down!

105
00:05:04,967 --> 00:05:05,833
Put your gun down.

106
00:05:06,767 --> 00:05:07,367
Put it down!

107
00:05:07,500 --> 00:05:08,833
Slowly!

108
00:05:10,067 --> 00:05:10,900
Zandro.

109
00:05:35,133 --> 00:05:36,067
Red.

110
00:05:41,567 --> 00:05:42,833
Is that for me?

111
00:05:44,100 --> 00:05:44,767
Yes.

112
00:05:45,633 --> 00:05:47,000
That's for you.

113
00:05:47,133 --> 00:05:48,200
Thank you.

114
00:05:48,333 --> 00:05:49,233
I got that over there.

115
00:05:49,367 --> 00:05:51,067
It's far away.
I got tired after picking that.

116
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:52,033
Really?

117
00:05:54,900 --> 00:05:55,467
You know what, Yen?

118
00:05:56,600 --> 00:05:58,433
I'm so happy that we've
fixed things between us.

119
00:06:00,600 --> 00:06:05,300
Promise me that from here on,
we'll always stay together.

120
00:06:05,433 --> 00:06:06,867
I promise, Red.

121
00:06:08,067 --> 00:06:10,000
From now on,

122
00:06:10,133 --> 00:06:12,367
I won't listen
to anyone but you.

123
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:13,933
I won't listen
to anyone else.

124
00:06:14,067 --> 00:06:15,933
I won't believe
whatever they say.

125
00:06:17,167 --> 00:06:20,833
And I won't let anyone destroy
our relationship.

126
00:06:23,833 --> 00:06:30,133
And I promise you,
I won't trust anyone easily.

127
00:06:30,267 --> 00:06:33,300
I won't listen to
whatever they say.

128
00:06:35,800 --> 00:06:36,767
You know what?

129
00:06:38,500 --> 00:06:41,900
You are my first and last love.

130
00:06:42,067 --> 00:06:47,100
And I don't want to be with
anyone else but you all my life.

131
00:06:48,967 --> 00:06:52,100
And you're my greatest love,
Yenyen.

132
00:06:52,233 --> 00:06:56,333
And I want to spend the
rest of my life loving you.

133
00:07:03,200 --> 00:07:06,000
I love being
on this island.

134
00:07:06,133 --> 00:07:08,833
It's far away from everything
that troubles us...

135
00:07:08,967 --> 00:07:10,767
from everyone fighting.

136
00:07:13,033 --> 00:07:19,767
Here, we realize more how
much we love each other.

137
00:07:19,933 --> 00:07:23,733
I wish we could
stay here forever.

138
00:07:25,200 --> 00:07:27,033
I like that too.

139
00:07:27,167 --> 00:07:30,500
But we have to go back
to our families.

140
00:07:31,567 --> 00:07:34,800
But this time,
we will be stronger.

141
00:07:35,800 --> 00:07:38,767
Like what I always say,
remember?

142
00:07:38,900 --> 00:07:41,800
- Never give up.
- Never give up.

143
00:07:41,933 --> 00:07:43,333
Yen, we will never give up.

144
00:07:44,800 --> 00:07:48,233
I'll die first before I ever
give up on us.

145
00:07:48,400 --> 00:07:49,500
Me, too.

146
00:07:50,767 --> 00:07:51,967
I will never give up.

147
00:08:02,267 --> 00:08:03,667
Take off your mask.

148
00:08:05,200 --> 00:08:06,700
Take it off!

149
00:08:13,533 --> 00:08:16,200
I know it's you, Rina.
I just want to see your face.

150
00:08:21,633 --> 00:08:23,400
Amanda...

151
00:08:23,533 --> 00:08:24,333
wow!

152
00:08:25,867 --> 00:08:28,700
You're so crazy.

153
00:08:30,400 --> 00:08:33,933
It took me a while
to prepare for this, Rina.

154
00:08:34,067 --> 00:08:35,333
You can't fool me anymore.

155
00:08:35,467 --> 00:08:38,233
You can't hurt me anymore.

156
00:08:38,367 --> 00:08:41,067
What's with that look, Zandro?

157
00:08:41,200 --> 00:08:41,933
Try to hit me.

158
00:08:42,067 --> 00:08:43,133
Come over here,

159
00:08:43,267 --> 00:08:45,000
- and I'll slap your face!
- Wait a minute! Shut up!

160
00:08:45,133 --> 00:08:47,100
I'll break your bones.

161
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:51,400
Try to kick me, and
I'll break your bones!

162
00:08:51,533 --> 00:08:52,567
Go on and laugh.

163
00:08:52,700 --> 00:08:53,633
We'll see.

164
00:08:54,933 --> 00:08:56,500
This will be the
end of you, Rina.

165
00:08:56,633 --> 00:08:57,967
You will lose everything.

166
00:08:58,100 --> 00:09:00,200
Everything you care about!

167
00:09:00,333 --> 00:09:05,300
Your money, your name,
and your family.

168
00:09:05,433 --> 00:09:06,333
Don't you believe me?

169
00:09:08,667 --> 00:09:10,500
I will ruin
everything you have.

170
00:09:10,633 --> 00:09:13,267
You won't have
anything left!

171
00:09:13,400 --> 00:09:15,500
Keep your mouth shut!

172
00:09:18,467 --> 00:09:19,300
I'm got scared.

173
00:09:19,433 --> 00:09:20,400
Oh, really?

174
00:09:20,533 --> 00:09:23,733
It's just you
and your husband!

175
00:09:23,867 --> 00:09:25,200
Who's holding a gun?

176
00:09:25,333 --> 00:09:26,267
It's us.

177
00:09:30,033 --> 00:09:31,000
Love, let's go.

178
00:09:31,133 --> 00:09:32,367
The police officers
are on their way here.

179
00:09:34,567 --> 00:09:36,233
You're going
to rot in jail!

180
00:09:36,367 --> 00:09:37,633
Get out of here.

181
00:09:37,767 --> 00:09:38,900
Not so fast.

182
00:09:41,733 --> 00:09:42,700
- Let's go.
- Hey!

183
00:09:42,833 --> 00:09:44,400
Come on.

184
00:09:44,533 --> 00:09:45,767
You guys should smile.

185
00:09:45,900 --> 00:09:47,033
Look over there.

186
00:09:50,300 --> 00:09:51,567
Zandro!

187
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,133
Zandro.

188
00:10:03,833 --> 00:10:04,767
Destroy that thing!

189
00:10:04,900 --> 00:10:05,733
How can I do that?

190
00:10:05,867 --> 00:10:07,133
Destroy it!

191
00:10:32,667 --> 00:10:34,033
What are we going to do now,
Zandro?

192
00:10:36,567 --> 00:10:38,633
We need to run, Rina.

193
00:10:38,767 --> 00:10:40,533
What if they see us?

194
00:10:40,667 --> 00:10:41,700
We have no other choice.

195
00:10:41,833 --> 00:10:42,833
We have to run.

196
00:10:43,733 --> 00:10:44,867
Come on, let's go.

197
00:10:49,600 --> 00:10:51,000
There they are! Get them!

198
00:10:51,133 --> 00:10:52,133
- Don't let them get away.
- There!

199
00:10:58,533 --> 00:10:59,533
Get in!

200
00:11:18,300 --> 00:11:20,767
Red, do you remember when
we were making shelter

201
00:11:20,900 --> 00:11:21,867
on this island before?

202
00:11:22,000 --> 00:11:23,067
Yes, I remember.

203
00:11:25,033 --> 00:11:26,533
You were mad at me back then.

204
00:11:26,667 --> 00:11:27,833
You didn't want me to help.

205
00:11:27,967 --> 00:11:30,533
But you were having a hard time.

206
00:11:30,667 --> 00:11:32,500
- No, I wasn't.
- No?

207
00:11:32,633 --> 00:11:34,067
But look at us now.

208
00:11:35,100 --> 00:11:38,667
- Upgraded!
- We upgraded our accommodation.

209
00:11:38,800 --> 00:11:40,800
We got all that we need.

210
00:11:43,700 --> 00:11:46,333
I've been here since yesterday.

211
00:11:47,333 --> 00:11:49,900
I thought the moment
I landed on this island,

212
00:11:50,033 --> 00:11:52,567
I will feel at peace.

213
00:11:53,867 --> 00:11:55,233
And joy.

214
00:11:56,733 --> 00:11:58,667
Like how we felt when
we were on the island.

215
00:12:00,233 --> 00:12:02,967
But I realized something.

216
00:12:03,100 --> 00:12:04,967
That I'm not happy
because of this place.

217
00:12:07,200 --> 00:12:10,133
I wasn't happy
because of the island.

218
00:12:11,367 --> 00:12:15,800
I was happy in this island
because...

219
00:12:15,967 --> 00:12:17,400
I was there with you.

220
00:12:23,000 --> 00:12:24,900
Me too, Yen.

221
00:12:25,033 --> 00:12:27,433
I'm so happy to be with you.

222
00:12:28,433 --> 00:12:30,233
And I will never leave you.

223
00:13:48,167 --> 00:13:48,667
Hey.

224
00:13:49,800 --> 00:13:52,167
I'm glad I didn't come back
for you yesterday.

225
00:13:52,300 --> 00:13:55,867
At least you two have
patched things up.

226
00:13:56,033 --> 00:13:57,933
Mister, you're so outspoken.

227
00:13:59,133 --> 00:14:00,833
I like that.

228
00:14:00,967 --> 00:14:02,133
Wait!

229
00:14:03,133 --> 00:14:06,867
I want to keep an image of
this island in my mind.

230
00:14:09,800 --> 00:14:11,600
Get in the frame. Come on!

231
00:14:18,567 --> 00:14:19,767
You know what?

232
00:14:19,900 --> 00:14:22,700
This island is so special to me.

233
00:14:24,133 --> 00:14:26,600
I will never forget this place.

234
00:14:26,733 --> 00:14:29,900
We met on this island.

235
00:14:30,067 --> 00:14:33,200
And this is where
we fell in love.

236
00:14:34,700 --> 00:14:41,933
And we also found our way back
to each other on this island.

237
00:14:42,067 --> 00:14:45,333
The next time we go
to an island,

238
00:14:45,467 --> 00:14:48,000
we'll say each other vows.

239
00:14:48,133 --> 00:14:50,133
Because we will get
married on that island.

240
00:14:51,333 --> 00:14:53,400
- I like that.
- You like that?

241
00:14:56,767 --> 00:14:57,633
Shall we?

242
00:14:59,367 --> 00:15:00,967
- Okay, fine.
- Fine.

243
00:15:01,100 --> 00:15:02,067
Let's go.

244
00:16:04,933 --> 00:16:05,900
Rina!

245
00:16:06,033 --> 00:16:07,567
What are you doing?
What's taking you so long?

246
00:16:07,700 --> 00:16:09,700
Hurry up!
We don't have much time left!

247
00:16:09,867 --> 00:16:12,400
I got tired from
running around.

248
00:16:13,833 --> 00:16:15,867
We were out all night.

249
00:16:16,833 --> 00:16:17,800
It's all your fault!

250
00:16:17,933 --> 00:16:20,133
Why did you do that, Zandro!

251
00:16:20,267 --> 00:16:22,133
Why did you shoot the policeman?

252
00:16:22,267 --> 00:16:23,400
What are you talking about?

253
00:16:23,533 --> 00:16:24,800
We were cornered!

254
00:16:24,933 --> 00:16:26,267
If I didn't shoot at them,

255
00:16:26,400 --> 00:16:28,633
you're probably getting booked
at the precinct now!

256
00:16:30,333 --> 00:16:33,333
Amanda and Lucho set us up!

257
00:16:33,467 --> 00:16:34,433
They did this to us!

258
00:16:34,567 --> 00:16:36,467
Those monsters!

259
00:16:36,600 --> 00:16:38,767
I will make them pay, Rina!

260
00:16:38,900 --> 00:16:42,567
They don't know what kind
of war they got themselves into.

261
00:16:42,733 --> 00:16:46,867
But before we can take revenge,
we have to hide for now.

262
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:48,233
What?

263
00:16:48,367 --> 00:16:49,233
Hide?

264
00:16:50,367 --> 00:16:55,233
Zandro, I can't hide in
your usual hideouts!

265
00:16:56,300 --> 00:16:58,300
The thing is,

266
00:16:58,433 --> 00:17:02,700
how can I tell Victor and Red
that I need to go into hiding?

267
00:17:02,833 --> 00:17:04,900
You're making too much
fuzz out of this!

268
00:17:05,033 --> 00:17:05,933
It's up to you!

269
00:17:06,067 --> 00:17:07,433
I'm leaving if you don't
want to come with me!

270
00:17:12,167 --> 00:17:13,267
Rina.

271
00:17:15,767 --> 00:17:18,100
What other secrets are
you hiding from me?

272
00:17:23,600 --> 00:17:24,567
Victor, this is a setup!

273
00:17:25,000 --> 00:17:26,867
Amanda and Lucho set me up!

274
00:17:27,000 --> 00:17:28,233
Those monsters!

275
00:17:28,367 --> 00:17:29,233
Horrible people!

276
00:17:30,500 --> 00:17:33,133
Why do you have to run if you
didn't do anything wrong?

277
00:17:33,267 --> 00:17:34,400
Tell the police!

278
00:17:36,100 --> 00:17:37,067
Victor, please.

279
00:17:37,200 --> 00:17:39,167
I have no time to explain right
now.

280
00:17:40,200 --> 00:17:41,733
I need to get my things
together.

281
00:17:42,767 --> 00:17:44,667
- I'm going to pack my bags.
- Rina.

282
00:17:44,800 --> 00:17:46,500
You're keeping something
from me.

283
00:17:46,633 --> 00:17:50,733
How can I help you if
you're not honest with me?

284
00:17:50,900 --> 00:17:55,967
Victor, can I explain later?

285
00:17:56,100 --> 00:17:58,033
I need to pack my bags.

286
00:18:06,167 --> 00:18:10,467
I'll talk to my mom
once we get home.

287
00:18:10,600 --> 00:18:14,633
We have to prepare
for our wedding.

288
00:18:14,767 --> 00:18:15,700
Really?

289
00:18:18,000 --> 00:18:19,133
But I'm excited too.

290
00:18:19,267 --> 00:18:20,733
I want to get married.

291
00:18:22,067 --> 00:18:26,867
But I'm afraid my mom
might cause us trouble.

292
00:18:27,000 --> 00:18:28,533
She might oppose the wedding.

293
00:18:29,667 --> 00:18:31,900
Don't be afraid, okay?

294
00:18:32,033 --> 00:18:34,300
We'll fix everything together.

295
00:18:35,967 --> 00:18:39,067
They'll see that we're meant
for each other...

296
00:18:39,200 --> 00:18:44,267
after all the challenges
and problems we've overcome.

297
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:46,833
Remember what I always tell you?

298
00:18:46,967 --> 00:18:48,233
Never give up.

299
00:18:48,367 --> 00:18:49,633
Never give up.

300
00:18:49,767 --> 00:18:54,100
We will prove to them that we're
meant for each other.

301
00:18:56,200 --> 00:18:57,933
Sir.

302
00:18:58,067 --> 00:18:58,867
Not right now, Emma.

303
00:18:59,000 --> 00:19:00,900
Sir, there are police officers
here.

304
00:19:09,733 --> 00:19:11,367
What can I help you with?

305
00:19:11,500 --> 00:19:13,700
We have a warrant of arrest
for Rina Ramos.

306
00:19:13,833 --> 00:19:15,400
She has to come to
the precinct with us.

307
00:19:17,233 --> 00:19:19,033
Why are you with them?

308
00:19:19,167 --> 00:19:21,333
Because I'm an eyewitness
to her crime.

309
00:19:23,367 --> 00:19:25,300
Surrender your wife.

310
00:19:25,433 --> 00:19:27,833
She has nowhere else to go.

311
00:19:30,033 --> 00:19:31,033
She's not here.

312
00:19:33,433 --> 00:19:36,567
They can arrest you for
obstruction of justice

313
00:19:36,700 --> 00:19:39,933
if you don't surrender
your wife.

314
00:19:42,067 --> 00:19:44,233
Sir, you should go inside.

315
00:19:44,367 --> 00:19:47,133
He's probably just trying
to distract us.

316
00:19:47,267 --> 00:19:48,500
She might be on the run by now.

317
00:19:48,633 --> 00:19:50,267
Okay. Search inside.

318
00:20:01,667 --> 00:20:02,700
Ma'am, don't try to run.

319
00:20:02,833 --> 00:20:03,767
We have a warrant of arrest
against you.

320
00:20:03,900 --> 00:20:05,367
No! No, no, no,
I'm not coming with you.

321
00:20:05,500 --> 00:20:06,567
No!

322
00:20:06,700 --> 00:20:08,000
Don't try to resist us.

323
00:20:08,133 --> 00:20:09,067
No, no, no!

324
00:20:09,200 --> 00:20:11,700
Don't touch me!
Don't touch me!

325
00:20:11,833 --> 00:20:13,300
Let me go!

326
00:20:13,433 --> 00:20:14,800
- Rina!
- Victor!

327
00:20:14,933 --> 00:20:17,900
- Don't worry!
- Let me go!

328
00:20:18,033 --> 00:20:19,867
- Let me talk to her.
- Let go of me!

329
00:20:20,000 --> 00:20:20,533
Rina.
Rina, I'll call a lawyer.

330
00:20:21,667 --> 00:20:22,700
Don't worry.
I'll be there for you.

331
00:20:22,833 --> 00:20:23,700
What is this?

332
00:20:23,833 --> 00:20:26,167
Justice is served.

333
00:20:28,800 --> 00:20:30,433
You're a monster, Amanda!

334
00:20:30,567 --> 00:20:31,767
You're a beast!

335
00:20:33,600 --> 00:20:35,400
Don't worry.

336
00:20:35,567 --> 00:20:36,467
- I'll take care of this.
- Mom?

337
00:20:36,600 --> 00:20:37,300
Mom?

338
00:20:37,433 --> 00:20:38,733
- What's going on?
- Red.

339
00:20:38,867 --> 00:20:40,133
I was set up, Red.

340
00:20:40,267 --> 00:20:42,567
I was set up.
It's all Amanda's doing!

341
00:20:42,700 --> 00:20:44,767
It's her fault!

342
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:48,033
The police won't arrest you
if you're innocent.

343
00:20:48,167 --> 00:20:51,800
You were caught in the act.

344
00:20:51,933 --> 00:20:54,233
You're so evil.

345
00:20:54,367 --> 00:20:55,833
You're the one who
has a criminal record.

346
00:20:55,967 --> 00:20:58,633
You're the bad guy here
and not me!

347
00:20:58,767 --> 00:21:00,600
Explain yourself
at the police station.

348
00:21:00,733 --> 00:21:01,800
Not to me.

349
00:21:01,933 --> 00:21:04,667
Am I getting this right?

350
00:21:04,800 --> 00:21:07,867
You're trying to get
Mommy Rina arrested?

351
00:21:08,000 --> 00:21:11,933
She's getting arrested
for frustrated murder

352
00:21:12,100 --> 00:21:15,633
and two counts
of frustrated homicide.

353
00:21:15,767 --> 00:21:17,667
Are you a lawyer now?

354
00:21:17,800 --> 00:21:19,900
You don't know what
you're talking about.

355
00:21:20,033 --> 00:21:21,233
Because you're
not a lawyer!

356
00:21:21,367 --> 00:21:22,267
Don't you want
to believe me?

357
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,933
Then ask the officers.

358
00:21:24,067 --> 00:21:25,333
She's telling the truth.

359
00:21:25,467 --> 00:21:27,467
That's what is stated on
your warrant of arrest.

360
00:21:27,600 --> 00:21:28,167
You have to come with us.

361
00:21:28,300 --> 00:21:29,200
Wait!

362
00:21:29,333 --> 00:21:30,300
You can't take my mom.

363
00:21:30,433 --> 00:21:32,133
She's innocent.

364
00:21:32,267 --> 00:21:33,233
She didn't do
anything wrong!

365
00:21:33,367 --> 00:21:35,200
You can explain in court.

366
00:21:35,333 --> 00:21:36,433
No, no.

367
00:21:36,567 --> 00:21:38,367
- Mom, don't go with them.
- I'm not coming with them.

368
00:21:38,500 --> 00:21:40,800
Just hold on to me.
Don't go with them.

369
00:21:40,933 --> 00:21:42,067
No!

370
00:21:42,233 --> 00:21:42,933
Stop!

371
00:21:44,267 --> 00:21:45,633
Miss Amanda.

372
00:21:45,767 --> 00:21:48,600
Please, don't do this,
Miss Amanda..

373
00:21:48,733 --> 00:21:50,300
She didn't do anything wrong.

374
00:21:50,433 --> 00:21:52,700
I'm begging you.

375
00:21:52,833 --> 00:21:54,933
Don't put my mom in jail.

376
00:21:55,067 --> 00:21:57,067
Stop getting revenge, please.

377
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:59,033
Revenge?

378
00:21:59,167 --> 00:22:02,200
You must be talking about
your mom and not me.

379
00:22:02,333 --> 00:22:04,100
I'm just doing the right thing.

380
00:22:05,733 --> 00:22:08,000
Your mom put me in jail before.

381
00:22:08,133 --> 00:22:11,667
You even told me you believe
that I'm innocent.

382
00:22:11,800 --> 00:22:14,367
Now, your mother will go to jail

383
00:22:14,500 --> 00:22:16,200
because she committed a crime.

384
00:22:16,367 --> 00:22:18,233
You're just taking revenge, Mom!

385
00:22:18,367 --> 00:22:20,400
Why are you doing this?

386
00:22:20,533 --> 00:22:22,433
Has your hatred already
consumed you?

387
00:22:22,567 --> 00:22:25,033
You should know the answer
to that, Eden.

388
00:22:27,600 --> 00:22:34,300
I suffered in jail when
I didn't do anything wrong.

389
00:22:34,433 --> 00:22:37,933
You grew up without me
by your side.

390
00:22:38,067 --> 00:22:40,533
So you should know how I feel.

391
00:22:40,667 --> 00:22:43,933
So, should I be happy
about this revenge?

392
00:22:44,067 --> 00:22:44,867
I don't know.

393
00:22:45,000 --> 00:22:47,000
What do you think?

394
00:22:47,133 --> 00:22:50,200
Karma did this to her.

395
00:22:50,367 --> 00:22:53,767
Whatever Rina is reaping now,

396
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:56,233
it's because of what she sowed.

397
00:22:56,367 --> 00:22:58,933
Karma has nothing to do
with this!

398
00:22:59,067 --> 00:23:01,100
You did all of this!

399
00:23:01,233 --> 00:23:02,667
This is your fault, Amanda!

400
00:23:02,800 --> 00:23:04,267
You're evil!

401
00:23:13,233 --> 00:23:15,800
Mom, you have to be strong.

402
00:23:15,933 --> 00:23:18,533
Why is Amanda doing this to me?

403
00:23:18,667 --> 00:23:22,667
I'm afraid she might try to take
you away from us, Eden.

404
00:23:22,833 --> 00:23:24,100
It's not going to happen.

405
00:23:24,233 --> 00:23:25,467
We're going to fight for her.

406
00:23:25,600 --> 00:23:27,467
We have no right to keep her.

407
00:23:27,600 --> 00:23:28,733
I'm here to take you home.

408
00:23:28,867 --> 00:23:30,733
Yenyen is not a child anymore
for you to decide for her.

409
00:23:30,867 --> 00:23:31,700
Who are you?

410
00:23:31,833 --> 00:23:32,967
You don't have a right!

411
00:23:33,100 --> 00:23:35,333
You're just her boyfriend,
and I'm her mom!

412
00:23:35,467 --> 00:23:36,400
I'm sorry, Mom.

413
00:23:36,533 --> 00:23:38,467
But I'm not leaving Red...

414
00:23:38,600 --> 00:23:40,567
especially Mommy Rina.

415
00:23:40,700 --> 00:23:43,600
I can't forget all the
good deeds they did for me

416
00:23:43,733 --> 00:23:45,467
when you abandoned me.

417
00:23:45,600 --> 00:23:47,467
We're going through
hard times right now.

418
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:50,067
But I think this is
the right time, Yen.

419
00:23:51,367 --> 00:23:52,733
Let's get married.
